BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260307T180259Z
DTSTART:20260323T040000Z
DTEND:20260323T050000Z
SUMMARY:Good Morning\, JoCo
DESCRIPTION:If there were a liiitle tiiiny bayyyybeee Jonathan Coulton who was just sleeping sooo soundly\, "Good Morning\, JoCo" is what you would say to wake him up\, so he could cheerfully start his day trying to escape from the terrarium where you keep him next to a scale model of the Gowanus Canal. "Good Morning\, JoCo" is ALSO a daily live-to-tape late-night-format morning show filmed in the Rolling Stone Lounge. The late night format comes from filming it right after the main concert each evening\, which is later at night. So listen here\, join your hosts River Butcher and Daphne Always and their surprise guests—and their planned guests like StormCenter5 Host Storm DiCostanzo. Come to our live taping for blue jokes\, stupid props\, jargon related to television production that may or may or not be necessary\, reshoots\, people wearing gnome hats\, and adult themes. We aren't checking ids\, but don't yell at us if someone drops a swear that's related to a complex topic you're not ready to explain to an audience member in your charge. And catch the finished show the next morning! Presented in glorious 1080p at a blistering 3\,000 kbps\, Good Morning JoCo is a PG-ish delight for the whole family when viewed in your stateroom.
CATEGORIES:READING / PERFORMANCE
LOCATION:Rolling Stone Lounge\, Deck 2\, Midship
SEQUENCE:0
UID:09444569fed2108b02c787714f7b7310
