SUMMARY:"Pride in Space" Dance Party
DESCRIPTION:And now\, a word from JoCo Cruise Partner Drew... "This year on Wednesday\, the 25th\, we'll be throwing our annual Pride party\, in March\, at the Sea View Pool. The theme for this year is "Pride in Space." In terms of the moodboard it is\, well\, space—and also The Pride of Chanur because of puns and because the cover is fabulous.  "It turns out that people wear party clothes in space when they're in atmosphere—e.g. when attending a soiree aboard the General Systems Vehicle\, the Empiricist—so I wouldn't stress too much about having the perfect thing to wear. But\, I'll also note that in space-space people wear space stuff or are maybe aliens. "And\, finally\, I'll note: LIONESSES (THE HANI) COMMAND STARSHIPS IN AN UNEASY INTERSPECIES INTERSTELLAR COMPACT AND THINGS DO NOT GET SIMPLER WHEN A HUMAN\, AN OUTSIDER\, SEEKS REFUGE ABOARD HANI CAPTAIN PYANFAR CHANUR'S VESSEL."
CATEGORIES:PARTY
