SUMMARY:(Not) Everybody’s a Critic
DESCRIPTION:Criticism is about giving perspective on art...but criticism is itself an art\, and the people who do it well are creating work of value. In this panel we’ll look at what criticism is\, its role as service journalism as well as critical evaluation\, who have been groundbreaking critics...and what it’s like when the critic hops over to the other side of the critical fence.
