SUMMARY:Transferable Skills
DESCRIPTION:Most writers “come up” or become best known for one sort of writing: journalism\, comics writing\, screenwriting\, etc. Then many of them try their hand and a different discipline of writing altogether. In this panel\, we look at what artistic and commercial skills learned in one field turn out to have application in another\, and which of these transferable skills might have been surprising to our panelists.
