SUMMARY:Deepfakes\, Manufactured Reality\, and How to Protect Yourself and Democracy
DESCRIPTION:AI-generated audio\, video\, and images are blurring the line between truth and fiction in ways that are already reshaping politics\, culture\, and public trust. Deepfakes are not just viral curiosities. They are tools that can be used to manipulate elections\, damage reputations\, inflame violence\, and undermine confidence in democratic institutions. Marginalized groups are often targeted first\, making this both a technology issue and a civil rights issue.
CATEGORIES:READING / PERFORMANCE
LOCATION:World Stage\, Deck 2\, Forward
